    "As observed experimentally, the relative abundances of hadrons follow the thermal distribution at common temperatures and baryonic chemical potentials, such that the thermal fit can fix the temperature and baryonic chemical potential [32].",
    "The temperatures of chemical freeze-out ( T ch for central Au+Au collisions at different col- lision energies are shown in Fig. 8.",
    "With increasing energy, the T ch increases and becomes constant at ∼ 160 MeV after √ s NN = 11.5 GeV.",
    "The parameters extracted from net-pro- ton higher moments [38] are also presented in the figure.",
    "They are consistent with the results from the hadron yield fit."
